===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|schewen|lang=enm}}, {{term|schawen|lang=enm}}, {{term|scheawen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|sceawian|scēawian|to look, look at, observe, gaze, behold, see, look on with favor, look favorably on, regard, have respect for, look at with care, consider, inspect, examine, scrutinize, reconnoiter, look out, look for, seek for, select, choose, provide, show (favor, respect, etc.), exhibit, display, grant, decree|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|skauwōnan||skawwōnan|to look, see|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|(s)ḱou-||(s)ḱeu-|to heed, look, feel, take note of|lang=en}}; see [[haw]], [[caveo]], [[caution]]. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|shaw||to show|lang=sco}}, {{etyl|frs|-}} {{term|scoe||to look, behold|lang=frs}}, Dutch {{term|schouwen||to inspect, view|lang=nl}}, German {{term|schauen||to see, behold|lang=de}}, {{etyl|da|-}} {{term|skue||to behold|lang=da}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|skygna||to spy, behold, see|lang=is}}, Albanian {{term|shkoj||I go|lang=sq}} related to {{term|shikoj||I see, observe, look for|lang=sq}}. Related to {{l|en|sheen}}.

